descriptionMd:
*Sharing Stories* is a series of interactive instructions that transforms Instagram’s promotional features into games, encounters, and poetic devices. Rather than starting from a finished work, the piece describes how to create itself and invites passing participants to create blooming color fields, poems out of found locations, and playful compositions using everyday data fragments. Taking place on a real Instagram account, subject to the whims of the algorithm, *Sharing Stories* embraces the harsh algorithmic environment that crowns viral moments in order to find spontaneous collaborators to co-opt these tools for unexpected and joyful connection.
&nbsp;
This project played out over 7 days on Alserkal Avenue’s Instagram account for their [“The feed is a stage”](https://www.instagram.com/p/DMxYdLqI5A1/) summer program, and culminated in 80+ artifacts created by over 100 players viewed by over 100,000 people. On the final day, I combined all the games and poll submissions into a single composite artifact, part collage of found Internet material and part live performance in response to audience participation.
&nbsp;
Read more on [Alserkal Avenue‘s announcement](https://alserkal.online/event/alserkal-avenue-instagram-becomes-a-stage-in-august/)
